    narr:narration """This hub collects ~15 **Resonance** rubric assessments across distinct pitch/narrative artifacts, each scoring how strongly the material lands through analogy, metaphor, founding story, and concrete example. The recurring verdict is *strong resonance via figurative grounding*: [Git/Kung-Fu analogies](narr:Assessment_Resonance_YC), the [GitHub-for-technical-founders analogy](narr:Assess_Resonance_RevenueModelTAM), [Matrix chips and 'a collaborator the mainframe guy'](narr:Rubric_Assess_Resonance), [Gods of Olympus + '75 decisions a day'](narr:Rubric_Resonance_FounderBetaUser), the [optometrist/phoropter extended analogy](narr:RubricAssess_Resonance_TXReview), and [flocking/particle-physics metaphors with a five-year-wait redemption arc](narr:RubricAssess_Resonance). Founding-story proof recurs — the ['deli email' chemistry signal](narr:Rubric_Resonance_YC_Call). Customer-grounded variants lean on real failure modes ([46/112 bugs, QA onboarding](narr:Rubric_Resonance_CustomerArchitect)) and direct quotes ([a design collaborator's mirrored consulting pain](narr:RubricAssess_Resonance_Sample1)). Framing devices recur: [WITH-vs-WITHOUT comparison](narr:Rubric_Resonance_YCDemoBeats), [the 'builder trap' reframe](narr:RubricAssess_Resonance_GTM), [steering-vector central metaphor](narr:Rubric_Resonance_ScarletDame).""" ;
